    "summary": "Paris L\u00f3pez-Marron is a young Mexican talent. His musical personality as pianist, orchestra/choir conductor and jazz arranger has taken him to give many concerts in the Netherlands, Germany, France, Belgium, Luxembourg, Poland and Mexico.\n\nParis L\u00f3pez Marr\u00f3n has participated in many international festivals such as:\n\n\u00b7 Trans-European Festival (France)\n. Stravinsky Festival (The Netherlands)\n\u00b7 Over the Borders Festival (Germany)\n\u00b7 Klanken Festival (The Netherlands)\n\u00b7 International Chamber Music Festival (Mexico)\n\u00b7 Het Parcours (The Netherlands)\n\u00b7 Musical June (Mexico)\n\u00b7 Jazz Masters (The Netherlands)\n\u00b7 Berkeley Jazz Fest (Mexico)\n\nHe studied piano at the music faculty of the University Veracruzana in Mexico.\nOne of his biggest success was to play the piano and conduct the orchestra at the same time performing Piano Concerto No.20 of W.A.Mozart, after which he got a very good feedback from his teachers and the public.\n\nIn 2007 Paris L\u00f3pez studied piano with Andreas Fr\u00f6hlich, Opera conducting and co-repetition with H\u00e9bert G\u00f6rtz, and classical singing with Johannes Green in Aachen, Germany and also with Donij van Doorn in Maastricht. \n\nHis most influencial piano teachers were: Alejandro Corona (Mexico),Avi Sch\u00f6nfeld (Israel), Jeroen Riemsdijk (The Netherlands).\n\nHis most influencial conducting teachers were: Roberto Lira (Mexico), Fernando Avila (Mexico), Francisco Sav\u00edn (Mexico), Enrique Bat\u00edz (Mexico), and Arian Tien (The Netherlands).\n\nAs a conductor, he won third prize at the 1st National Competition for Orchestra Conductors organized by CONACULTA in Mexico.\n\nIn 2009 Paris studied conducting with Arian Tien, (Tilburg) jazz composition and arrangement with Wolfgang Braun, and piano at the Conservatory in Maastricht with Jeroen Riemsdijk. In June 2011 Paris got his Master's degree in Piano and has been succesfully working in The Netherlands and Germany as pianist, dirigent and piano teacher since.",
